&gt; 
&gt;&gt;Presumably you need to retrieve that subset before PUTting a modified
&gt; 
&gt; version back, 
&gt; 
&gt;&gt;even if you already have the full representation from the main resource.  
&gt;&gt;(To get the ETag for the subset resource.)  
&gt; 
&gt; Use HEAD, I think that will/should return the ETag.

Sure, but then you have no guarantee that the ETag you see on HEAD 
matches the data version that you GOT from the primary URI.

A; GET primary URI (get value X for field Y)
B: PUT primary URI
A: HEAD subset URI (get ETag corresponding to B&#39;s update of value Z for 
field Y)
A: PUT to subset URI (sending ETag, overwriting B&#39;s update)

